$ fsutil file

{ Create a new file (of possibly zero size) #fsutil-file-createNew

  `→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/fsutil_exe[fsutil] file createNew` can be used in → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] or → Windows/PowerShell to create a file with a given size.

   The following to commands create an empty file and a file whose size 42 bytes. `fsutil` fills the 42 bytes with a zero (`0x00`) value.
code {
C:\> fsutil file createNew → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Local/Temp[%temp%]\empty.txt  0
C:\> fsutil file createNew → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Local/Temp[%temp%]\42.txt    42
code }

  See also the → Linux/shell/commands/touch[Linux shell command `touch`].

}
